1 olive oil
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 cucumber
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet Diced Chicken
1 packet tomato paste
20 g butter
¼ cup water
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Corn Chips
1 sachet Mexican Fiesta spice blend
1 packet BBQ sauce

• Roughly chop baby spinach leaves and cucumber. Drain the sweetcorn.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook sweetcorn until lightly
browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are “popping” out.

• SPICY! You may find the spice blend hot! Add less if you're sensitive to heat.
• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is
hot, cook diced chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked
through, 5-6 minutes.
• Return charred corn to the pan, then add Mexican Fiesta spice blend and
tomato paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add BBQ sauce, the butter and water.
Simmer, until slightly thickened, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

• Meanwhile, combine cucumber, baby spinach, slaw mix, mayonnaise
and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl. Season
to taste.

• Divide creamy spinach slaw between bowls.
• Top with Mexican-spiced chicken and corn.
• Serve with corn chips. Enjoy!